<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
    Entitlements for the Mac App Store distribution build only.
    The Developer ID (notarized) build uses Glotty-Release.entitlements
    (empty), which is correct for non-sandboxed distribution.

    Sandbox is mandatory for App Store. Selection grab still works
    inside the sandbox because TCC (the privacy framework that
    governs Accessibility) is independent of the sandbox boundary —
    same Accessibility permission flow the user is already familiar
    with. Network client lets the LLM provider HTTP calls reach
    OpenAI / DeepSeek / etc. without further user prompts.

    NOT included:
      com.apple.security.get-task-allow — would block notarization
      and is rejected for App Store too (same reason: debug-attach
      entitlement doesn't belong in shipped software).

    Open questions Apple Review will decide for us:
      - Dictionary Services (DCSGetActiveDictionaries via dlsym):
        likely flagged as private API. If rejected, we'll need to
        guard those calls behind `#if !APPSTORE` and ship a build
        without the dictionary section.
      - Fn-leader hotkey via CGEventTap: may or may not work in
        sandbox; haven't tested. If broken, switch to
        RegisterEventHotKey with a Cmd+Shift+T/P/E/C chord.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
